(1)
131, 133-139, 141, 145 East 43rd Street, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Lexington Avenue. No. 141 is St. Agnes' parsonage (Roman Catholic) adjoining the church. The clearing in the foreground is the future site of the
Chrysler Building.
November 11, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, the following spring, a closer view excluding almost
all of the church.
March 18, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.

143, 141-133, 133-129 East 43rd Street, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of Lexington Avenue: an aerial view showing the Graybar Building on the west side of Lexington Avenue and the New York Central Building, No. 230 Park Avenue.
Januery 31, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, a much closer view, showing St. Agnes' parsonage and Church (Roman Catholic), but not including all of the latter.
